    {
      "segments": [
        {
          "scid": "an4.1:1.1",
          "pli": "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—",
          "en": "So I have heard. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an4.1:1.2",
          "pli": "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā vajjīsu viharati bhaṇḍagāme. ",
          "en": "At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Vajjis at the village of Bhaṇḍa. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an4.1:1.3",
          "pli": "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi: ",
          "en": "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an4.1:1.4",
          "pli": "“bhikkhavo”ti. ",
          "en": "“Mendicants!” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an4.1:1.5",
          "pli": "“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ. ",
          "en": "“Venerable sir,” they replied. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an4.1:1.6",
          "pli": "Bhagavā etadavoca: ",
          "en": "The Buddha said this: "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an4.1:2.1",
          "pli": "“Catunnaṃ, bhikkhave, dhammānaṃ ananubodhā appaṭivedhā evamidaṃ dīghamaddhānaṃ sandhāvitaṃ saṃsaritaṃ mamañceva tumhākañca. ",
          "en": "“Mendicants, not understanding and not penetrating four things, both you and I have wandered and transmigrated for such a very long time. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an4.1:2.2",
          "pli": "Katamesaṃ catunnaṃ? ",
          "en": "What four? "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an4.1:2.3",
          "pli": "Ariyassa, bhikkhave, sīlassa ananubodhā appaṭivedhā evamidaṃ dīghamaddhānaṃ sandhāvitaṃ saṃsaritaṃ mamañceva tumhākañca. ",
          "en": "Noble ethics, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an4.1:2.4",
          "pli": "Ariyassa, bhikkhave, samādhissa ananubodhā appaṭivedhā evamidaṃ dīghamaddhānaṃ sandhāvitaṃ saṃsaritaṃ mamañceva tumhākañca. ",
          "en": "immersion, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an4.1:2.5",
          "pli": "Ariyāya, bhikkhave, paññāya ananubodhā appaṭivedhā evamidaṃ dīghamaddhānaṃ sandhāvitaṃ saṃsaritaṃ mamañceva tumhākañca. ",
          "en": "wisdom, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an4.1:2.6",
          "pli": "Ariyāya, bhikkhave, vimuttiyā ananubodhā appaṭivedhā evamidaṃ dīghamaddhānaṃ sandhāvitaṃ saṃsaritaṃ mamañceva tumhākañca. ",
          "en": "and freedom. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an4.1:2.7",
          "pli": "Tayidaṃ, bhikkhave, ariyaṃ sīlaṃ anubuddhaṃ paṭividdhaṃ, ariyo samādhi anubuddho paṭividdho, ariyā paññā anubuddhā paṭividdhā, ariyā vimutti anubuddhā paṭividdhā, ucchinnā bhavataṇhā, khīṇā bhavanetti, natthi dāni punabbhavo”ti. ",
          "en": "These noble ethics, immersion, wisdom, and freedom have been understood and comprehended. Craving for continued existence has been cut off; the attachment to continued existence is ended; now there are no more future lives.” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an4.1:3.1",
          "pli": "Idamavoca bhagavā. ",
          "en": "That is what the Buddha said. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an4.1:3.2",
          "pli": "Idaṃ vatvāna sugato athāparaṃ etadavoca satthā: ",
          "en": "Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say: "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an4.1:4.1",
          "pli": "“Sīlaṃ samādhi paññā ca, ",
          "en": "“Ethics, immersion, and wisdom, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an4.1:4.2",
          "pli": "vimutti ca anuttarā; ",
          "en": "and the supreme freedom: "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an4.1:4.3",
          "pli": "Anubuddhā ime dhammā, ",
          "en": "these things have been understood "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an4.1:4.4",
          "pli": "gotamena yasassinā. ",
          "en": "by Gotama the renowned. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an4.1:5.1",
          "pli": "Iti buddho abhiññāya, ",
          "en": "And so the Buddha, having insight, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an4.1:5.2",
          "pli": "dhammamakkhāsi bhikkhunaṃ; ",
          "en": "explained this teaching to the mendicants. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an4.1:5.3",
          "pli": "Dukkhassantakaro satthā, ",
          "en": "The teacher made an end of suffering, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an4.1:5.4",
          "pli": "cakkhumā parinibbuto”ti. ",
          "en": "seeing clearly, he is extinguished.” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an4.1:5.5",
          "pli": "Paṭhamaṃ. ",
          "en": ""
        }
      ],
